 *** How to generate ssh key in client machine    :- ssh-keygen
     * ssh-keygen,  after run this command we got a key pairs (private & public keys), private key client side me usi user k pas rahti h or public key ko server k pas copy krna hota h, copy eske liye cmd (ssh-copy-id username@ipaddress)
     
     Ex. :- ssh-copy-id ritik@192.168.1.10
             Es command ko chalate hi ssh public key jisme save h wo folder (.ssh) client side se copy hoke server side me paste ho jata h or .ssh k andar ki file jisme ssh public key save h wo (id_rsa.pub) rename ho krke (authorized_keys) ho jati h.
     
   **Where private and public is getting stored in client machine
   
     -- ssh key alws stores in users home dir  
       Ex. :- if a user name is harry then, --- private /home/harry/.ssh/id_rsa & public key /home/harry/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
       
    **Note :- root user has home directory as /root/.ssh/{id_rsa,id_rsa.pub}
    
    
 ***To copy a.txt file from client to server             --->>scp a.txt ritik@192.168.1.3:/home/ritik/        (To copy a folder use -r)
 
 ***To download a.txt file from server to client         --->>scp ritik@192.168.1.3:/home/ritik/a.txt .        (To copy a folder use -r)
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 *** DNS(Domaine Name System)(Name Server) :- It is as same as Contact book
 
 Jab hm kisi website ko pahli bar (uske domain name k through) connect krte hn to hme us web ki ip chahiye hoti h, to hamara laptop sabse pahle apne hi cache memory me web ki ip search krta h, ip n milne pr router ki cache memory pr web ki ip search krta h, because we are searching for this web at first time so there is no ip of searched web in laptop's & router's cache memory. So router domain name k sath DNS k pas jata h or agar DNS k pas searched domain name exist krta h to DNS router ko usi domain k ip batata h or router pahle us ip ko DNS k jaise hi domain name k sath save kr leta h or fir laptop ko us web ki ip bata deta h or fir laptop bhi us ip ko DNS k jaise hi save kr leta h or fir router ko ip batata h or fir NAT k use krke router hme us server tak pahucha deta h or server router ko uska response deta h or router fir user ko response krta h.
 
 Agar wahi user thode time bad fir se wahi web search krta h to ab uska DNS us user k system hi hoga, kyoki wo system bhi kuchh time k liye DNS k jaise hi domain k sath ip save kr leta h.
 
 Or agar ab us router se connected koi dusra user kuchh din me hi pahli bar wahi web search krta h jo pahla user kiya tha to bhi uske liye router fir se main DNS k server k pas nhi jayega, wo khud ek DNS k jaise hi kaam karega or apne pas save data me us domain ko search karega or ip nikal k us user k system ko bta dega.
 
 
   Q1 :- ky router k cache memory me ip milne k baad bhi router us ip ko system k pas bhejta h y nhi.
     Ans:- hn router us ip ko system k pas bhejega, kyu system ki request hi yhi thi ki use us domain ki IP chahiye or tab router hi DNS tha.
     
     
   Q2 :- Pahli bar kisi web ko search krne pr (system-->>router-->>DNS-->>router-->>system-->>router-->>server-->>router-->>system) system us ip ko router ko batata h y fir nhi.
     Ans:- hn system ko router se ip milne k baad bhi system router ko ip k sath ye bhi batata h ki use kaun s protocol use krna h, eska mtlb system fir se router ko ip batata h.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
