     Creating an instance---- 
     
        **  At first create an A/c on AWS, then login with root user on console pannel & then go with EC2 option to create an instance.
        **  Click "Launch instance" btn & start providing instance name, OS, version of OS, instance type, key pair to create a new instance.
         Access your instance ----
        **1 "**ssh -i Downloads/mykey.pem ubuntu@100.26.155.241**" cmd to aces your instance by using ssh key (without using/creating pass)  
        
            * Your file of ssh key (mykey.pem) must have in "/home/ritik/Downloads" dir.
            * Your working location must have current user's home dir (/home/ritik).
            
        **2 "**ssh ubuntu@100.26.155.241**" commad to access your instance by using password (without using ssh keys).
            
            * "sudo passwd ubuntu"                                         :- command to set new password for your aws machine.
            * "sudo vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/60-cloudimg-settings.conf"  :- edit this file, wrote yes in place of no.
            * "sudo systemctl restart ssh"                                 :- command used to restart the SSH (Secure Shell) service.
            * then logout and login into your aws machine by password.
            
