                 <<<<<<<<<<<<<-------  Adding extra valume  ------->>>>>>>>>>>>>
                 
        Storage :- yha apna data store hota h.     ye 3 type k hote hn.
        
      1. Block Storage :- * Esme data chahe jitna bda ho ye, use chote-2 block me store krta h, ek block ki size 4kb se 4mb tak ho skti h.
                          * Or esme data store krne k liye blocks ko kisi sequence me n rakh kr kisi random location me rakh diya jata h.
                          * Jab stored data ko use krte hn to usse related sare blocks ordr me ake us data ko complte krk hme provide krta h.
                          ** Or jab hm window me koi new valume create krte hn, to hme storage update krne ko bola jata h eska mtlb ye data  
                             ko delete nhi krta h, but puri storage me blocks ko ek formate me arenge krte ek empty valume create krta h.
                          * Ye small blocks k karan bahut fast hota h, share or use krne me.
                             
      2. File Storage :- * Esme data diffrente files me small blocks k andar store hota h.
                         * File storage ek bar me multiple OS k sath attach ho skta h.
                         * Ye block storage se thoda slow hota h.
                         
                         
      3. Object Storage:-* Esme object (data) ki jitni size hoti h utni hi size k blocks me data store rahta h.
                         * mtlb agr data 20gb k h to wo 20gb k hi block me store hoga.
                         * eske liye OS required h but ye only ek hi OS support kr sakta h.  Ex. google drive
                         * mtlb agr esme store data ko kisi dusre OS me use krta h to pahle 1st OS se es storage ko dittach krta padega.
                         * Or ye File storage se thoda slow hota h, because agr koi 1gb k data trnsfr ho rha h to jab tak wo pura trnsfr nhi
                           ho jata koi bhi dusra data trnsfr nhi ho skta h chahe wo only 1mb k hi ho.
                           
      Storages in AWS :- 
                   1. Amazon EBS (Amazon Elastic Block Storage)
                   2. Amazon EFS (Amazon File System)
                   3. Amazon S3  (Amazon Simple Storage Service)
                   
      Attaching sxtra volume------
      
           lsblk :- cmd to check all storages
           
           Go to Volumes section -->> Create volume -->> (type gp3, 10gb, iops 3000, Throughput 125, Ava zone check carefully, Create Volume)
           Select created vol -->> Actions -->> Attach volume -->> (select instance where attach it, device name, Attach volume) Done...
           
      Partition of Volume-------   agar kisi volume me ek file crupt ho rhi h to us file se related files bhi crupt hona suru ho jati hn.
                                   aise me boot file bhi crupt hone lagti h or pura OS crupt ho jata h jisse server hi band ho jata h.
                                   esi liye partition jaroori h or boot file k to bahut hi jyada. esse ek data dusare se isolate rahta h.
                                     
           1. MBR (Master Boot Record):-  "fdisk" cmd used for partition in MBR
                                      esme max partition 2tb tak hi ho skta h.
               i. Primary partition:- ye totelly isolated hote hn.   Ex. c,d,e,f drive.
                                      Primary partitions ko ek sath 3 hi bna skte ho. or max 4 hi bna skte hn.
               ii.Extended partition:- ye totelly isolated nhi hota h, eske andar hm bahut sare folder (partition) bna skte hn.
                                        agar extended partition krna h to primary max 3 hi hone chahiye.
                                        
           2. GPT (GUID Partition table):- "gdisk" cmd used for partition in GPT
                                           esme hm 128 primary partitons bna skte hn.
                                           esme hm 9zb [(9*10^12)gb] tak k partition kr skte hn.
                                           
           Steps of partition of 10Gb storage (xvdf)----------
                "sudo fdisk /dev/xvdf" -->> m -->> n -->> p -->> 1 -->> 2048 -->> +5G -->> p -->> w  ||
                
	   "sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/xvdf1" --->>> Command to creating file system
	   "sudo mount /dev/xvdf1 /mnt" -->>> Command to attach this partition
	   then "cd /mnt" -->> "sudo mkdir A B C D" -->> "sudo touch hello"
	   
	   now dittach the volume & create a new instance with the extra networking setting (subnet same reson of volume) then attach the 
	   volume with new instance & now just mount the volume with mnt. Then you can get the partition & 4 dirs & 1 file created into mnt.
           
