     <<<<<<<<<<<---- Cloud Watch ------>>>>>>>>>>>>
     
  Cloud watch k use krke hm kisi bhi Instance ki monitering ko check kr skte hn ye kaam to hm EC2 me bhi inst ko select kr k kr skte hn.
  Cloud watch me Matrics me all matrics me EC2 me sare active or recent inactive instances ki monitorring ko bhi mention kiya gya h ab hme 
   jis bhi instance ki monitorring krni h uski id search krkr filter kr lena h bs.
   
  Hm esse ye to jaan skte hn ki Hamare instance me ky ho rha h or abhi tak ky hua h but use hone se pahle kaise roka jaye eske liye hm 
  "Cloud Watch" me ek cheej or padenge jiska name h "Alarm", ese hme monitorring ki kisi mertics me set krna h or jab ye ek particular 
  paramiter ko pass karega to ye Alarm hit ho jayega.
  
  How to set a Alarm??
  Create alarm ==>> select metrics ==>> EC2 ==>> Per-Instance-Metrics, now copy that instance's id (where you want to add this alarm) and
   paste there to filter the metrics of that instance now choose one matrics (CPU Utilization) to add there alarm ==>> Select metrics ,
   and set there "Greater & Equal" and 50% of CPU Utilization to hit this alarm ==>> Next, remove notification section also (chargable),
   ==>> Next , named your alarm ==>> Next ==>> Create Alarm ||
   
   
   <<<<<<<<<<<------- /var/log ------->>>>>>>>>>>>              (eske andar users ki activity save hoti h.)
   
   
    "/var/log/apache2/error.log" :- agar galti se /var/www/html/index.html file delete ho jati h, or koi user instance ki ip dal kr use
     dekhna chahta h to kyuki waha pr file hi nhi h to use error milegi or agr koi bhi error aati h to wo esi file me save hoti h.
     
    "/var/log/apache2/access.log" :- es file k andar us user ki ip or bahut sari cheeje hoti hn. jaise agr kisi ne hamare instance me chal
                                      rhe web ko access kiya to uski sari details hamare pas aayegi
    ab agr pta krna h ki hamari web ko kitni bar search kiya gya h mtlb abhi tk kitna traffic aaya h to eske liye hm access.log me lines ko 
    count krke pta kr skte hn. bcs user k access krne pr user ki sari details access.log pr save ho jati h.
    
    
    EC2 :- Infrastructure as a service. (Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud)
    RDS :- Relational Data-Base Services, ye ek database services h 
    S3  :-(Software as a services) Simple Storage Services, y Amazon ki ek service h, jo 1-2GB tk free h, esme data 99.999..% secure rahta h.
    DynamoDB:- ye bhi Amazon ki ek service h, jisme data Non-tabular(NoSQL) form me rahta h.
    Lambda:- ye ek Platform as a service h, esme hm apna code dalte hn or kuchh bhi kam krwa skte hn, wo code chahe html,js,python, y fir 
             jiska bhi ho ye sb kuchh support krta h, wo hme jiski hm chahte hn uski machine create krke de deta h.
    Elastic Beanstalk:- ye Amazon ki ek aisi service h jo hme jaroorat k hisab se instance bhi create kr dega or agr or accha server chahiye
                        to ye load balancer bhi create krke de dega, ese use krne k to koi charge nhi h but ye jo kuchhh bhi create krega 
                        agr wo chargable h to ye uska bhi charge lega.
         
         
