      <<<<<<<<<<<<<<----------  Docker  ----------->>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
      
   First tool of DevOps => Docker
   
   Man lo hamare pas ek python k code h or use run krna h to uske liye hme ek VM banana padega or usme python k setup krna padega fir usme 
    code run kr skte hn es pure kam me 30 min se jyada time lagega, or ab agr kisi ne bol diya ki mere pas JAVA k code h to fir se uske setup
    me utna hi time lagega or hm apne system me bhi limited VM hi bna skte hn jiska mtlb ye hn ki ye sari cheeje bahut complex hone wali hn
    to ese hi solve krne k liye Docker bna h ye within 1 min me hi sara setup krke hamara koi bhi code run kr skta h.
    
    
    
                            VM                                       Docker
                            
                 Guest OS(Kernal) presents                     System k Kernal use kr leta h.
                 Total ISO file size 4.7GB                     Totel ISO(Docker Image) file size 1.5GB
                 Time consuming                                Time saving
                 Every OS supports it shoftly                  Only Linux supports docker
                 
    But Every OS supports "Docker Desktop"             
    Container run karane wale tools :-  Docker*, Podman, Rocket, Crio 
    
    Docker       :-   Engine, that run/create container
    Container    :-   VM
    Docker image :-   ISO file
    Docker registry :- Where docker images are stored  (DockerHub)
    
    
    ECR (Elastic Container Registry) :- Amazon docker registry
    ACR (Azure Container Registry) :- Azore docker registry
    
    Installation of Docker in Ubuntu :-
    
           1. sudo apt update
           2. sudo apt install docker.io
           3. sudo docker version/--version
           4. sudo docker ps          :- To show how many containers are running now.
              sudo docker ps -a       :- to show all running or previous run docker containers.
              sudo docker ps -aq      :- to show all running containers id only
           5. sudo docker pull ubuntu :- to download docker image.
           6. sudo docker images      :- to show all images.
           7. docker run ubuntu date  :- to create an OS to run date command.
           8. docker run ubuntu sleep 15:- to run a container for 15sec (but 15 sec tak hm terminal k use bhi nhi kr skte hn.)
           9. docker run -d ubuntu sleep 15:- to run a container for 15sec in background (abhi hm apna terminal use kr skte hn.)
           10. docker run -d --name ritik ubuntu sleep 300:- run a container by naming it, itself.
           11. docker exec -it ritik bash :- to go into container, usk andr kam krn k liy shell chahiye to shell k name, agr cntnr chalu h to
           12. docker run -it --name ritik1 ubuntu bash:- ye container chalta hi rahega kyu ki ese kamm hi yhi mila h ki bash shell chala k
                                                          rakhega, ye container tab tak chalega jab tak hm container ko Ctrl+c nhi krte.
           13. docker start/stop cntnr name/id :- to start/stop a stopped/started container. id k ek do digit bhi likh skte hn but unique ho.
           14. docker rm container name/id :- to delete stopped containers. multiple k liye space dekr name/id likhna hota h.
           15. docker rmi image-name :- to delete docker image, nam k bad tag bhi likha jata h nhi to by default ye latst ko delete kr deta h
           16. docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq) :- cmd to remove all running containers.
           17. docker tag myimage newimage :- to create a new image (newimage) with having same data of our old created image (myimage)
           
           
           Or agr koi container kisi image k through running h to tab tak docker image ko delete nhi kiya ja skta h.
                                                          
           "-it" use krne se hm container banate hi uske andar chale jate hn, uske andar alag se jana nhi padta h.
           "Ctrl + p + q" :- container ko band kiye bina container se bahar aane k liye ye short key use hoti hn.
           
           docker run alpine ping google.com :- ping cmd ko bina install kiye "Alpine" OS se chalana.
           
           
           
