     <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<  -----------------  Creating own "Docker Image" with our requirements ---------- >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
     
     
     Man lo hme koi setup krna h or wo hme daily chahiye, uske liye hmne docker image se ek container banaya or usme apn setup kr liya lekin
      jaise hi hm container delete krenge or fir se new container create karenge to hme fir se apna setup krna padega.
     To es problem k ek solution ye h ki jis container me hmne apna setup kiya tha usi container ki ek Image create kr le, jisse hamari ek 
      apni Image create ho jayegi or ab jo bhi container hm create karenge usme apni new created Image k use karenge or es bar hamare new 
      created container me hamara sara setup pahle se hi rahega..
      
      STEPS ---------
      
     ** first create a container which id starts with f7d44,now install here ncal cmd and create some directories at here. And now create an
         image of this container by using following cmd.....
      
     ** docker commit docker-name/id new-image-name :-   cmd to create new docker image(updated ISO file) by a running container
        (docker commit f7d44 myimage)
        
     ** Now create a new container by using our new created image (myimage) by cmd (docker run -it myimage bash) and now you are are able to
         run "cal" cmd and ls here to see your created directories.
         
         
     Or ab man lo hmne 2-3 ghante me koi ek setup kiya h or ab bahut sare system me wahi same setup krna h to hme fir se sabhi k liye 2-3 
      ghante lagenge, to eske liye ek solution h jiska name h "Docker Hub" jaha pr hm apni Images ko store kr skte hn.
      
     
     How to push your newlly created docker image at Docker Hub------------
     STEPS------------
     
     ** "docker login" cmd to login on your Docker Hub ac by CLI, now enter your user-name and password to login here.
     ** "docker tag myimage username/myimage" cmd to rename our created image because image name must start with your dockerhub user name.
     ** "docker push username/myimage" cmd to push your image globlly at Docker Hub.
     
     Or ab meri es image (ritiksingh06/myimage) ko globally koi bhi pull kr skta h or usse use kr skta h.
     Docker Hub me hm only 1 repo private rakh skte hn 1 se jyada private rakhne k liye ac upgrade krna padega.
     
     Task :- Run a C code on your container and create an image of this container and share the link of your docker image.
     
         first install gcc compiler to compile the code of C then write the code of C in sample.c file now compile the code written in 
           sample.c by using command "gcc -o demo sample.c" and now run this compiled code "demo" by cmd "./demo"      ||DONE||
     
     
     
  ***************************************************************.*****************************************************************
  
  
      "usermod -aG docker username" :- cmd to add a user into "docker" group, which added user can use any cmd without using sudo word at fst
         
     TASK :- first create a container by using ubuntu docker image, and into this container install gcc compiler of C and add a code of C in
              a file named count.c and now compile the C code with cmd "gcc -o count count.c" and then you got a new file "count" of compiled
              C code, now copy your file "count" at /bin then you are able to run your c code by only type "count" at your terminal.
             Now create an image (ritiksingh06/count) of this container and push this image at Docker Hub.
             
             
   <<<<<<<<<< Docker File >>>>>>>  
   
      Es ek file me wo sare steps likhe hote hn jo hm manually krte hn, image use krke container banana or container me setup krke fir se 
       uski ek image banana, ye sare steps hm ek hi file me note down krke use run kr denge or hme ek image create ho kr mil jayegi.
         
         
         
         
         
         
         
         ky load balacer k bhi domain name hota h. agr hnn to fir ky un instances k domain name nhi hota jo LB k through connect rahte hn???
         
  Steps in written in "Dockerfile" file, your file must have this code to execute it's code.-------------
         
      1.  "FROM gcc"               :- "FROM" is use to download/get image from docker hub, so we need gcc compiler, so we write gcc at there.
      2.  "COPY count.c /"         :- "COPY" word is used for coping file "count.c" at home dir(/) of our container.
      3.  "RUN gcc -o count /count.c" :- "Run" is used to run a command to compile the the C code of file count.c and store at file count.
      4.  'CMD ["/count"]'         :- "CMD" is used to run a dedicated command when we run a container using this image.
      
     ** "docker build -t newimage ." :- Now run this cmd to create an image by your code & dot (.) represents the path of your Dockerfile.
        "docker build -t newimage -f mydockerfile"
     ** "docker run newimage" :- Now run this cmd to run a container by using newimage & then suddenly you get the output of your C code 
                                  because you mentioned there a dedicated cmd jo ki, us image ko use krke container banate hi run ho jayegi.
                                  
     By default "docker build" cmd run krne pr ye "Dockerfile" name ki docker file ko hi run krke image create krta h. but agr aapki 
      docker file kisi dusre name se h to aapko ek extention add krna hoga, (-f mydockerfile)
      
             
  ***************************************************************.*****************************************************************
  Set up apache server by creating Docker file with docker image (httpd)
  
      * first create a html file must have name "index.html", and now create a Docker file with following elements:
             "FROM httpd"
             "COPY index.html /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/"
      *"docker build -t myweb ." cmd to build docker image.
      *"docker run -d -p 1133:80 myweb" cmd to run a container by using image "myweb", at port no. 1133.
      
      to see your web, these are Urls:- "localhost:1131", "127.0.0.0:1131", "public-ip:1131" & "dockercontainer-ip:1131".
      
      
      
             
  ***************************************************************.*****************************************************************
  Set up Worldpress server by docker container, with AWS mysql RDS database, by using "worldpress" docker image.
  
  * first create a mysql database on AWS. let DB name = worldpress, user = admin, password = Q12345678.
  * "docker run -d --name wordpress -e WORDPRESS_DB_HOST='....(fill end point here)....' -e WORDPRESS_DB_USER=admin -e WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD
     =Q12345678 -e WORDPRESS_DB_NAME=wordpress -p 1155:80 wordpress"
  
  Or ab browser me "public-ip:1155" search krke waha user create krke aasani se wordpress use kr skte hn.
  
  "docker volume create myvol"   :- cmd to create a new volume named "myvol"
  "docker volume ls"             :- cmd to show all docker volumes
  "docker volume rm volume-name" :- cmd to remove a docker volume
  "docker run -itd -v myvol:/mnt ubuntu" :- cmd to add this volume(myvol) with a new container.
  
  Now go into the created container and at /mnt and create some folder&files at there.
  or ab es container ko delete kr dena h, or fir dusra container banakr usi volume "myvol" ko usse connect kr dena h, previous commands k use
    krke, or fir hm /mnt pr jakar dekhenge to waha pr hamari created sare folders&files whi pr dikh jayengi.
    
  Docker me 3 type k network hote hn, we can see all these by using cmd "docker network ls" :-- bridge, host, none
  "docker run -itd --network none ubuntu" :-command to create container with network "none".
                                            It has no ip we can check it's IP by "docker inspect hc | grep IPA"
  by default jab hm container banate hn to usme "bridge network" use hota h.
                 
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
